## useReactive Basic Usage Example

```javascript
import { useReactive } from 'ahooks';

const MyComponent = () => {
  const state = useReactive({
    count: 0,
    inputVal: '',
    obj: { value: '' },
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <p>state.count: {state.count}</p>
      <button onClick={() => state.count++}>Increment</button>
      <button onClick={() => state.count--}>Decrement</button>
      <input value={state.inputVal} onChange={(e) => state.inputVal = e.target.value} />
      <p>state.inputVal: {state.inputVal}</p>
      <input value={state.obj.value} onChange={(e) => state.obj.value = e.target.value} />
      <p>state.obj.value: {state.obj.value}</p>
    </div>
  );
};
```

## useMap API Reference

```APIDOC
useMap<K,V>(initialValue?): [Map<K, V>, { set: (key: K, value: V) => void; get: (key: K) => V | undefined; setAll: (newMap: Iterable<[K, V]>) => void; remove: (key: K) => void; reset: () => void }]

Parameters:
  initialValue: Optional. The initial value for the Map. Accepts an Iterable of key-value pairs.
    Type: Iterable<[K, V]>
    Default: undefined

Returns:
  A tuple containing:
  - map: The current Map object.
    Type: Map<K, V>
  - methods: An object containing utility functions for managing the Map:
    - set: Adds or updates an element in the Map.
      Signature: (key: K, value: V) => void
    - get: Retrieves an element from the Map by its key.
      Signature: (key: K) => V | undefined
    - setAll: Replaces the entire Map with a new one from an iterable.
      Signature: (newMap: Iterable<[K, V]>) => void
    - remove: Removes an element from the Map by its key.
      Signature: (key: K) => void
    - reset: Resets the Map to its initial value.
      Signature: () => void
```
